      "content": "While the lifecycle mining and blade recycling of wind turbines are valid concerns, they are far less severe than the continuous, global pollution caused by fossil fuel extraction and combustion. The embodied carbon in wind energy is typically only about 10 to 20 grams of CO2-equivalent per kilowatt-hour, which is an order of magnitude lower than that of natural gas. Therefore, the environmental benefits of wind energy overwhelmingly outweigh the material waste issues, especially when considering that natural gas operations involve constant methane leaks and air pollution.",
